Senator Adeleke Olorunnimbe Mamora, Minister of State for Health, congratulated All Progressives Congress National Leader Bola Tinubu on his election as the party’s presidential flag bearer on Thursday. Mamora’s congratulations were contained in a letter addressed personally to the former governor of Lagos State. Tinubu defeated Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, former Transportation Minister Rotimi Amaechi, and 12 other presidential candidates to win the APC ticket. Also Read: APC Ticket: Oshiomhole Hails Tinubu “You have led from the front as a leader and have come thus far to the glory of God. The real battle still lies ahead in 2023. “As you march on with confidence, may your troops be willing in your day of battle and may God’s purpose for your life be fulfilled. Congratulations, my leader.”